airlines. some tourist attractions that are run by the archaeological survey of india have different rates for indians and foreigners. these rates are prominently posted at the entrance and ticketing booths. the rates for foreigners may be as many as five to ten times those for indians. this is understandable due to the much lower average cost of living in india. likewise, if you are reserving a hotel room or an airline ticket over the internet, you may find that paying in dollars costs significantly higher. you can get an indian friend to book in rupees and in most cases, 